Throughout all versions
- improve debugging and commenting
- refactor when reasonable
- conform all names to Zend naming convention detailed at: http://framework.zend.com/manual/1.12/en/coding-standard.naming-conventions.html

0.1.2
- Downloading and Downloaded filters are switched! Downloaded shows torrents in progress and completed ones until next browser refresh; Downloading always shows only completed ones.
- fix Episodes Only config toggle
- remove all NMT support (only supported OS is currently Debian 7.5)
- clean up all the undefined variable PHP notices spewing into the web server error_log
- repair phone.css button bar location so it floats just above bottom edge of screen even when scrolling
- fix New Favorite Last Downloaded Episode: one input field splits into two but doesn't understand SSxEE notation
- prepopulate global default seed ratio in New Favorite
- completely add or completely remove normalizing feature from guess_match() to detectMatch()
- fix annoying bug where browser thinks Cmd is still depressed after switching to browser using Cmd-Tab on Macs
- fix titles when added to Favorites via toolbar button so that episode number is not included in title
- pin the Favorites dialog so that it is easier to manage Favorites in bulk
- strip season and episode data from title when using Add to Favorites button in toolbar
- pin the Feeds tab in the Configuration dialog
- add Feed Title input above each Feed URL
- add config option "Videos Only" beneath "Episodes Only" to only show items with at least one video quality
- Downloading and Downloaded filters are redundant with each other due to progress bar--combine into one filter called Downloads and use color-coding to distinguish downloading from downloaded items
- Transmission filter is redundant with Transmission modal window and Downloading and Downloaded--remove Transmission filter
- fix the filterBar so that it wraps properly when screen is narrow (responsive design, may not be necessary with removal of filters)
- fix feed section header numbers so that they match the number of rows after selected filter has been applied
- if torrent is deleted using contextMenu, the clientButtons delete and trash buttons sometimes don't know about it until the page is refreshed
- how does <li id="id_###"> get its class overridden for downloading/downloaded items and why does clientID not match id when it happens?
- fix Downloaded items staying in Downloading filter (possibly by merging the two filters)
- resolve collision between $torInfo in html.php and torInfo() in tools.php
  - $torInfo has $torInfo['dlStatus'] but torInfo() has status codes
  - fixed typo of $torInfo['clientId'] in html.php
  - removed now-defined but still unused $torInfo['clientId'] in feed_item.tpl
  - fixed infoDiv's display when $torInfo is not set--now displays if $torInfo['dlStatus'] != ''

